en_62198_0	The Commonwealth Local Government Forum in an article to the Financial Times has said that Sri Lanka which has put a stop to the scourge of terrorism & is now perusing the avenues of peace should be criticized constructively along with stintless support.
en_62198_1	According to a representative of the CLGF the Commonwealth should assist Sri Lanka to build up a post war democratic framework.
en_62198_2	It also states that the upcoming Commonwealth State Leaders meeting which is slated to be held in Colombo shortly should be a consortium of state leaders which also includes the participation of grass root level & civil society activists.
en_62198_3	The CLGF which comes under the purview of the Commonwealth Secretariat has initiated several programmes in Sri Lanka with the aim of assisting war ravaged countries in their post war recovery.
